<p><strong>[<span style="color: grey"><span class="odate time_1517670011 format_%25e%20%25b%20%25Y%2C%20%25H%3A%25M%7Cagohover">03 Feb 2018 15:00</span></span>] [<span style="color: green">+156</span>]</strong></p>
</div>
    
    
    
    </div>
<p>I had this idea for a Meta-Mafia &#8212; organized fictional crime. I was thinking about the disposal of fictional evidence when it occurred to me how handy it would be if you could dispose of <em>real</em> evidence this way.</p>
<p>Most of the work that followed was figuring out the details. If you store a body in <em>Hamlet</em>, is it in every copy? What about translations of <em>Hamlet</em> &#8212; will it show up there too? Can I store the bodies in any work? Can I write fanfiction just to store bodies in? Etc. Once I got all that sorted, I decided to dump the Meta-Mafia idea (which would have made the article more comedic) and use the excellent <a href="/chicago-spirit">Chicago Spirit</a> instead (which made it spookier and tragic).</p>
<p>This piece also contains one of my personal favorite hooks: <em>Foundation personnel embedded in literary and academic circles are to be briefed on SCP-3138; they are to report any fictional work discovered to deviate from its canonical number of human corpses.</em></p>
<p>I mean, <em>come on</em>. That's a fucking fantastic opening line.</p>
</div>
</div>
</div>
<br />
<strong>[<a href="/scp-3241">SCP-3241</a>] [<a href="https://youtu.be/b2_Kx1y3lyE">♬</a>] &#8212; <em><a href="/scp-3241">The SS Sommerfeld</a></em></strong><br />
<span style="white-space: pre-wrap;">&#32;&#32;&#32;&#32;</span><em>Have you ever seen a Scranton Reality Anchor go critical? I have. Words like &quot;Biblical&quot; come to mind.</em>
<div class="collapsible-block">
<div class="collapsible-block-folded"><a class="collapsible-block-link" href="javascript:;"> ►&nbsp;Commentary</a></div>
<div class="collapsible-block-unfolded" style="display:none">
