<p><strong>[<span style="color: grey"><span class="odate time_1587860060 format_%25e%20%25b%20%25Y%2C%20%25H%3A%25M%7Cagohover">26 Apr 2020 00:14</span></span>] [<span style="color: green">+109</span>]</strong></p>
</div>
    
    
    
    </div>
<p>I wrote this for <span class="printuser avatarhover"><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/uraniumempire" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(1613974); return false;"><img class="small" src="http://www.wikidot.com/avatar.php?userid=1613974&amp;amp;size=small&amp;amp;timestamp=1609721445" alt="UraniumEmpire" style="background-image:url(http://www.wikidot.com/userkarma.php?u=1613974)" /></a><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/uraniumempire" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(1613974); return false;">UraniumEmpire</a></span>'s <a href="http://www.scp-wiki.net/forum/t-13262147/writing-challenge-impostor-syndrome">Imposter Syndrome</a> contest &#8212; specifically, 'aping' the style of <span class="printuser avatarhover"><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/cadavercommander" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(3187823); return false;"><img class="small" src="http://www.wikidot.com/avatar.php?userid=3187823&amp;amp;size=small&amp;amp;timestamp=1609721445" alt="CadaverCommander" style="background-image:url(http://www.wikidot.com/userkarma.php?u=3187823)" /></a><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/cadavercommander" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(3187823); return false;">CadaverCommander</a></span>. In truth, I kind of cheated &#8212; I didn't aim to replicate his prose-style, but rather, just went with an old draft of mine that I thought had a very strong 'CadaverCommander' vibe to it. I retooled it for the contest.</p>
<p>The idea of this little anomalous Studebaker that manages to avoid capture at every turn &#8212; not through 'magic', but just through sheer savvy and knowledge of the terrain &#8212; has been baking in the back of my head for quite a while, now. I also just loved the angle of having the UIU realize they should leave it alone, then the Foundation stepping in thinking 'UIUseless, we GOT this' &#8212; only to then realize too late that they absolutely DO NOT 'got this'.</p>
<p>Anyway, the whole premise is (at least in part) based off the life and times of <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Popcorn_Sutton">Popcorn Sutton</a>, a notorious moon-shiner. The car is active in the territory he was known for operating in, and the anomaly's date corresponds to the date of his death (March 16th).</p>
<p>This is one of the only articles I've written which uses the BHS. I used it here 'cuz Cadaver uses it in all of HIS articles, and I was trying to replicate his 'aesthetic'.</p>
</div>
</div>
</div>
