<p><strong>[<span style="color: grey"><span class="odate time_1564883487 format_%25e%20%25b%20%25Y%2C%20%25H%3A%25M%7Cagohover">04 Aug 2019 01:51</span></span>] [<span style="color: green">+162</span>]</strong></p>
</div>
    
    
    
    </div>
<p>Not even a day after I wrote Abwesenheit, I wrote this one. It just came to me in a rush while reading about deep-sea diving and all the various cautionary steps you need to take in order for your body to adjust to the appropriate pressures (decompression sickness is no fuckin' joke). Once I started thinking about things like neoteny and axolotl, the article practically wrote itself. Based off the very real (and very horrible!) <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Byford_Dolphin#Diving_bell_accident">Byford Dolphin incident</a>.</p>
<p>Oh, and thanks go to <span class="printuser avatarhover"><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/peppersghost" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(1553042); return false;"><img class="small" src="http://www.wikidot.com/avatar.php?userid=1553042&amp;amp;size=small&amp;amp;timestamp=1609721446" alt="PeppersGhost" style="background-image:url(http://www.wikidot.com/userkarma.php?u=1553042)" /></a><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/peppersghost" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(1553042); return false;">PeppersGhost</a></span> for pointing out the easy-pick for the theme song.</p>
